{% if use_ddd %}
## Package Structure (DDD-Oriented)

```text
src/main/java/{{ base_package | replace('.', '/') }}/
├── config/                  # Spring wiring, infrastructure beans, external client config
├── web/                     # REST controllers, exception handlers, transport-only concerns
├── web/dto/                 # Request and response models
├── domain/                  # Entities, value objects, domain services, domain exceptions
├── service/                 # Application services / use-case orchestration
├── repository/              # Persistence adapters and Spring Data repositories
└── security/                # Filters, auth converters, security config
```

### Boundary Rules

- `domain/` must not depend on `web/`.
- `web/` must never call repositories directly.
- `repository/` maps between persistence representation and domain objects if necessary.
- `service/` is the transaction boundary for write use cases.
- Security adapters expose the authenticated principal in a form the service layer can consume without servlet-specific coupling.

{% else %}
## Package Structure (Standard Layered)

```text
src/main/java/{{ base_package | replace('.', '/') }}/
├── config/                  # Configuration properties and bean wiring
├── web/                     # Controllers and exception advice
├── web/dto/                 # Transport DTOs
├── service/                 # Business logic and transactional orchestration
├── domain/                  # Core entities and enums
├── repository/              # Spring Data repositories and custom persistence logic
└── security/                # Security config and authentication helpers
```

### Layer Responsibilities

- `web/`: receive HTTP input, validate DTOs, delegate once, return HTTP responses
- `service/`: own business rules, transactions, and interactions across repositories
- `repository/`: own JPA access patterns and custom queries
- `domain/`: hold the ubiquitous language and invariant-bearing model
- `config/`: register infrastructure without leaking framework details across the codebase

{% endif %}

